## 2026-03-27 - Bulk-rename regex has no ReDoS protection
- Added `isSafeRegex()` guard in `token-store.ts` that rejects patterns longer than 200 chars or containing nested quantifiers (the primary cause of catastrophic backtracking). Called before `new RegExp()` in `bulkRename`.
- Route handler in `tokens.ts` now returns 400 (not 500) for rejected/invalid regex patterns so the UI shows a clear error message.
- Files changed: `packages/server/src/services/token-store.ts` ~L16 (isSafeRegex helper), ~L930 (guard in bulkRename); `packages/server/src/routes/tokens.ts` ~L172 (400 status for regex errors)

